Some might recall the rueful lesson of the Trojan War: “Beware of Greeks bearing gifts.” The rueful lesson of our own time: “Beware of geeks bearing gifts.” Yes, Big Brother walks among us now, peeking and snooping into everything. And we, innocently and unwittingly, invited Big Brother into our midst. Fourth, it’s not an accident that these Silicon Valley companies are supporters of Barack Obama. The greatest among these Obama supporters is Eric Schmidt, executive chairman of the largest of these companies, Google. Message.Title: Why Stocks are Down
Message.Msg: Simple reason -- with the retail investor gone, the same manipulative jackasses that buy the stock and artifically take it to unreasonable levels are the ones that control the price down. The retail investor used to be the shock absorber that has been gone for a few years now. Mix in an inept regulatory framework (rampant insider trading, frontrunning, etc) and an alarmist media (rates going to 2.25%, bloody murder!) and you have the potion for extreme market volatility. Of course, don't forget helicopter Ben who artifically tries to prop the market with promise of bond buying to continue to the 2014 only to break it. For the few retail investors left, the only way to succeed is to buy a market leader at a decent multiple and hold on to it for a long time (2-3 years)
